cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and sequence-to-sequence (Seq2Seq) architecture. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to update Knowledge Graphs (KG) from text. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a novel Seq2Seq architecture for generating KG operations. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with extracting information from text-based game transitions to build KGs. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also relevant as the paper discusses updating KGs, which are a type of database, from text.
